<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-056-094  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 056 094.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Network World  Jan 8 1990 v7 n2 p15(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>AGS software lets traders access data from one PC. (AGSInformation Services Inc.'s The Platform) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Desmond, Paul.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>AGC Information Services unveils The Platform, a Unix-basedfinancial trading application software package which itco-developed with Data Logic Ltd and which is comprised of fourcomponents: Applications Management, Market Data Management,Message Management and Distribution, and Systems Administrationand Management.andP;  Price of The Platform is dependent uponconfiguration, ranging from $7,000 to $10,000 per traderworkstation.andP;  The Platform lets traders in financial institutionsaccess multiple data sources from their workstations.andP;  Users canadditionally extract data from those sources with The Platform'sapplication programming interfaces and insert the data into aspreadsheet or similar program.andP;  All four components can runeither on the same processor or multiple processors.andP;  Users cancustomize screens so they can glean only the information they needfrom their sources.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   AGS Information Services Inc. (product introduction)Data Logic Ltd. (products).andO;Product:   Platform (Computer program) (product introduction).andO;Topic:     Data ManagementAccess MethodsFinancial TerminalsData BasesProduct IntroductionFinancial SoftwareOn-Line Searching.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>